node.title: Homicide inquiry launched after man's body found in river
node.description: Police have named the man found by a member of the public in a Waikato river on Tuesday afternoon, sparking a homicide investigation.
node.content:
["Police have named the man found in a Waikato river this week, sparking a homicide investigation, as 40-year-old Abdul Kareem of Mangere.", "", "
The Whangamarino River and wetlands. (File pic) Photo: DOC
", "Officers want to hear from anyone who used the boat ramp to the Whangamarino River on Island Block Road on Tuesday.", "They also want to speak to those who were near the road or Island Block Road Bridge from midday to five in the evening the same day.", "Kareem was found by a member of the public on Tuesday afternoon.", "Information can be provided to the police via 105, or anonymously to Crime Stoppers on 0800 555 111, quoting file number 220215/4486."]
